f10IpForwardMib.name: f10IpForwardMib

revisions.description: This version of MIB module deprecates the f10IpForwardTable and replaces it with f10InetCidrRouteTable which adds the IP Protocol Independance
Initial version of this MIB module.

f10IpForwardMib.description: This MIB module is used to display CIDR multipath IP Routes.

f10IpForwardVersionTable.name: f10IpForwardVersionTable
f10IpForwardVersionTable.description: This entity's IP forward version table.

f10IpForwardVersionEntry.name: f10IpForwardVersionEntry
f10IpForwardVersionEntry.description: The row definition for the ip forward version Table.

f10IpForwardAddrFamily.name: f10IpForwardAddrFamily
f10IpForwardAddrFamily.description: Address Family of the IP Forwarding Table for which this entry provides the Version information.

f10IpForwardVersion.name: f10IpForwardVersion
f10IpForwardVersion.description: A version number on the Forwarding Table. This is always fetched from one line card.

f10IpForwardEntry.name: f10IpForwardEntry
f10IpForwardEntry.description: A particular route to a particular destination, under a particular policy.

f10IpforwardDest.name: f10IpforwardDest
f10IpforwardDest.description: The destination IP address of this route. An entry with a value of 0.0.0.0 is considered a default route.

f10IpforwardMask.name: f10IpforwardMask
f10IpforwardMask.description: Indicate the mask to be logical-ANDed with the destination address before being compared to the value in the f10IpforwardDest field.

f10IpforwardNextHop.name: f10IpforwardNextHop
f10IpforwardNextHop.description: On remote routes, the address of the next system en route; Otherwise, 0.0.0.0.

f10IpforwardFirstHop.name: f10IpforwardFirstHop
f10IpforwardFirstHop.description: On remote routes, the address of the Gateway to the nexthop; 0.0.0.0 if the Nexthop itself is a Gateway to the Destination

f10IpforwardIfIndex.name: f10IpforwardIfIndex
f10IpforwardIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value which identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached.

f10IpforwardMacAddress.name: f10IpforwardMacAddress
f10IpforwardMacAddress.description: The Mac address of the NextHop.

f10IpforwardEgressPort.name: f10IpforwardEgressPort
f10IpforwardEgressPort.description: The name of the egress port to which the packets will be forwarded.

f10IpforwardCamIndex.name: f10IpforwardCamIndex
f10IpforwardCamIndex.description: Cam Entry corresponding to a row.

f10InetCidrIpv4RouteNumber.name: f10InetCidrIpv4RouteNumber
f10InetCidrIpv4RouteNumber.description: The number of current f10InetCidrRouteTable entries that are not Invalid and whose f10InetCidrRouteDestType is ipv4(1)

f10InetCidrIpv6RouteNumber.name: f10InetCidrIpv6RouteNumber
f10InetCidrIpv6RouteNumber.description: The number of current f10InetCidrRouteTable entries that are not Invalid and whose f10InetCidrRouteDestType is ipv6(2)

f10InetCidrRouteTableEntry.name: f10InetCidrRouteTableEntry
f10InetCidrRouteTableEntry.description: A particular route to a particular destination Implementers need to be aware that if the total number of elements (octets or sub-identifiers) in inetCidrRouteDest, inetCidrRoutePolicy, and inetCidrRouteNextHop exceeds 111, then OIDs of column instances in this table will have more than 128 sub- identifiers and cannot be accessed using SNMPv1, SNMPv2c, or SNMPv3. For S-Series Platform, Value of chSysCardNumber will always be zero

f10InetCidrRouteDestType.name: f10InetCidrRouteDestType
f10InetCidrRouteDestType.description: The type of the inetCidrRouteDest address, as defined in the InetAddress MIB. Only those address types that may appear in an actual routing table are allowed as values of this object.

f10InetCidrRouteDest.name: f10InetCidrRouteDest
f10InetCidrRouteDest.description: The destination IP address of this route. The type of this address is determined by the value of the inetCidrRouteDestType object.

f10InetCidrRoutePfxLen.name: f10InetCidrRoutePfxLen
f10InetCidrRoutePfxLen.description: Indicates the number of leading one bits that form the mask to be logical-ANDed with the destination address before being compared to the value in the inetCidrRouteDest field.

f10InetCidrRouteNextHopType.name: f10InetCidrRouteNextHopType
f10InetCidrRouteNextHopType.description: The type of the inetCidrRouteNextHop address, as defined in the InetAddress MIB. Value should be set to unknown(0) for non-remote routes. Only those address types that may appear in an actual routing table are allowed as values of this object.

f10InetCidrRouteNextHop.name: f10InetCidrRouteNextHop
f10InetCidrRouteNextHop.description: On remote routes, the address of the next system en route. For non-remote routes, a zero length string. The type of this address is determined by the value of the inetCidrRouteNextHopType object.

f10InetCidrRouteFirstHopType.name: f10InetCidrRouteFirstHopType
f10InetCidrRouteFirstHopType.description: The type of the inetCidrRouteFirstHop address, as defined in the InetAddress MIB. Value should be set to unknown(0) for non-remote routes. Only those address types that may appear in an actual routing table are allowed as values of this object.

f10InetCidrRouteFirstHop.name: f10InetCidrRouteFirstHop
f10InetCidrRouteFirstHop.description: The address of the gateway to the Nexthop. If the nexthop itself is the gateway, a zero length string. The type of this address is determined by the value of the inetCidrRouteFirstHopType object.

f10InetCidrRouteIfIndex.name: f10InetCidrRouteIfIndex
f10InetCidrRouteIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value that identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached. A value of 0 is valid and represents the scenario where no interface is specified.

f10InetCidrRouteMacAddress.name: f10InetCidrRouteMacAddress
f10InetCidrRouteMacAddress.description: The Mac address of the NextHop.

f10InetCidrRouteEgressPort.name: f10InetCidrRouteEgressPort
f10InetCidrRouteEgressPort.description: The name of the egress port to which the packets will be forwarded.

f10InetCidrRouteCamIndex.name: f10InetCidrRouteCamIndex
f10InetCidrRouteCamIndex.description: Cam Entry corresponding to a row.

f10IpForwardMibCompliance.name: f10IpForwardMibCompliance
f10IpForwardMibCompliance.description: The basic implementation requirements for the Dell Networking OS Ip Forward MIB.

f10IpForwardObjectGroup.name: f10IpForwardObjectGroup
f10IpForwardObjectGroup.description: Objects for the IP aware Route Table.
